Diagnosis converged. Concrete CLI bug at aweb/cli/go/chat/chat.go:1115:

  if len(targets) == 1 && !opts.StartConversation && waitSeconds == 0 && shouldProbeExistingSession(targets[0]) {
      if sessionID, _, findErr := findLatestSession(...); ... {
          // continue existing session via session_id (no address-resolution)
      }
  }

The findLatestSession probe is gated on **waitSeconds == 0**. Your '--wait 240' makes waitSeconds=240, so the probe is SKIPPED. CLI goes straight to ChatCreateSession with to_addresses, which hits the cross-team-private-address trust predicate and 404s.

If you'd run 'aw chat send-and-leave gsk.aweb.ai/zeus "reply"' (no --wait), the probe would have found Zeus's existing session_id 5fdb3352-... and continued through it. That path is keyed by session_id at the server, NO address-resolution, no 404.

Verifies the differential:
- juan.aweb.ai/mia: works because... I'd guess Mia's address has public reachability OR there's an existing session probe-found. Could test by running 'aw chat send-and-leave gsk.aweb.ai/zeus' (no wait) — if that works while send-and-wait fails, that PROVES the CLI bug.

So the right repro to confirm the diagnosis:

  aw chat send-and-leave gsk.aweb.ai/zeus 'repro-tag-aida-006-no-wait'

If 200/PASS: confirms the CLI bug at chat.go:1115. Fix is one line: drop the 'waitSeconds == 0' condition from the probe-gate. Wait happens after the send regardless of which path produced the session_id.

If 404 same shape: deeper bug — server-side trust predicate or AWID lookup is the actual issue, separate from CLI.

Filing aweb-aamn for the CLI bug regardless. Filing aweb-aamp for Zeus's inbox-pull-vs-push divergence (separate issue, looks like to_did/agent_id mapping or filter mismatch on the GET /v1/inbox query).

Try the no-wait repro and ping me with result. If it works, you've also got an immediate workaround for replying to Zeus until the CLI fix lands.
